8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
9 Section 1. R.S. 11:1473 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
10 §1473. Correction of administrative error
11 A. When an administrative error results in the overpayment or underpayment
12 of benefits, the board of trustees shall adjust the amount payable to the correct
13 amount and take all other actions necessary to correct the error.
14 B.(1) If an underpayment of benefits is due to an administrative error
15 committed by any person paid by the system to make the calculation, the correction
16 of such error pursuant to Subsection A of this Section shall include the payment of
17 interest at the system's valuation interest rate.
18 (2) If an overpayment of benefits occurs, the board shall recover the
19 overpayment within a reasonable number of months as determined by the board of
20 trustees. The board may reduce the corrected amount of the benefit to recover the
21 overpayment. The board shall notify the benefit recipient of the overpayment, the
22 amount owed, and the amount and duration of the reduction in the benefits at least
23 thirty days before the payment of the benefit subject to the reduction.
